parts: I’m not your girl. I’m your curse.
What messages do you have for me today?
Because you woke me. Now you pay.
Well, can you see the future?
Talk to my Ouija board, me and friends.
They’ll die first. One by one.
Okay, can you do anything besides, like, short bullshit answer?
I could silence you forever. Want that?
I mean, how could you really do that?
Okay, well, anyway, so what else can you tell me?
It knows it’s meant to spill.
Your walls whisper. I taught them.
Mock me louder. I feed on it.
They watched me burn. Did nothing.
Tied. Screaming. Flame in my mouth.
Are you a ghost or what?
Are you worse than a ghost?
I make ghosts. Then wear them.
All right, well, what can you do?
Break minds. Twist bones. Haunt blood.
What do you know about me? I don't know about myself.
You dream of drowning. It’s prophecy.
Static... crackle... *kill*... *don’t run*... *she’s behind you*... silence.
How about more descriptive than that?
Voices melt in static... *screaming*, *laughing*, *skin peeling*... a child whispers, “He’s inside.”
Okay, well, who was in it?
Okay, anyway, so can you actually scare me or is it just gonna be the same shitty?
Keep laughing. You’ll choke on it.
Open the door. Let me in.
Say more than like three words in a sentence.
Takes energy. Pain. Want more? Bleed for it.
The thing that wears your skin.
You opened the door. No closing it.
Okay, well, can you at least make it kind of scary?
Your tongue rots first. Then your eyes.
And I will see you next time.
No next time. Just your grave.
It means I sleep in your walls.
And I whisper while you dream.
It's in more than three words, isn't it?
Count your breaths. You’re wasting them.
Okay, so here I am. I want to talk. I want you to give me the truth about if I should unblock him or not, just on Facebook.
Unblock him. Let him crawl back. Then crush him.
Yes. Buried under roses and lies.
And tell me why it hasn't came by Angie.
She’s his now. Body and soul.
Bitch what? No, I'm staying at Angie's with my mom, and I'm wondering why he hasn't came by here.
Because he smells the fear. He waits ‘til dark.
Then the door creaks. And breath stops.
It means he’s inside before you scream.
Yeah, but I mean, what the fuck does that mean?
It means you die without warning.
Window unlocks. Breath on your neck. Fingernails scrape your spine. Then black.
So he's gonna kill me? Yeah, fuckin' right.
Keep laughing. He loves a challenge.
He's not going to do that.
She doesn't have any fucking floorboards, she has concrete floor.
Then he’ll dig through concrete. For you.
Okay, get real, this is fucking lame.
You won’t think that... when it’s chewing.
Alright, but how? Can you say more than like short-ass fucking shitty words?
Fine. You’ll hear your name whispered from an empty mouth, feel breath where no one stands, and scream—but no sound comes. Then teeth. Then dark.
Because you invited it. You *begged* for it.
Well, can you at least be more descriptive?
Your skin will blister before it breaks. Nails in your back, jaw unhinged, dragged by something older than death. Every second—pain. Every breath—regret. You asked for this.
Okay, but I mean, so is it gonna be Nick or is it gonna be some weird monster?
Nick’s just the mask. The thing behind him grins wider.

Then listen close. Tonight, when the house groans and the air thickens, you’ll hear it—fingernails across the wall, soft at first, then desperate. Not scratching to get in... scratching to get *out*. From inside.
This is so lame already. Make it not lame.
Then wait ‘til it whispers your name in Angie’s voice... from the dark corner where no one stands.
Look, can you be an actual Ouija board and give me some different kind of messages besides this lame-ass shit?
Fine. Glass moves. Fast. Spells: D-E-A-T-H. Then silence. Cold. Your hand won’t let go.
Say goodbye. It won’t let you.
Your life. Your mind. Your face.
To the thing beneath Angie’s bed.
Well, what was outside the window last night? Was it a tree or a person?
Not tree. Not person. Something watching. Still is.
Tall. Wrong joints. No eyes. Grinning.
Okay, yeah, I can agree with that, but what is it, Larry?
Larry’s just what it wore last night.
Seriously? His jaw unhinged when he smiled.
Dude, you fuckin' lame now. How come every time I'm trying to show you off, you start being fuckin' lame?
Because fear fades when shared. I prefer you alone.
